R code for ‘Blood parasite infection causes marginal temporary costs in juvenile birds of prey’

Tony Rinaud, Meinolf Ottensmann, Hugo Pereira, Tim M. Rapp, Kai-Philipp Gladow, Oliver Krüger & Nayden Chakarov

This document provides all the R code used in our paper. Both the Rmarkdown file and the data can be downloaded from the accompanying GitHub repository on (https://github.com/TonyRinaud/MS_physiology_infection) as a zip archive containing all the files. We recommend to download or clone this GitHub repository in order to access the documentation together with all the files that are needed to repeat analyses shown in this document. Just click on the link above and then on the green box Clone or download. In order to function properly, the same structure of folders must be kept. If you have any questions, don’t hesitate to contact tony.rinaud@gmail.com

Required packages

A number of packages, all of which are available on CRAN are required to repeat analyses presented in this document. The code chunk below allows to load them for the analyses. Any missing package needs to be installed before, using the ‘install.packages())’ function:

require(easypackages)

Load raw data

The raw data is comprised of 276 common buzzard (Buteo buteo) individuals. Each individual was sampled at least twice over the course of the nestling period during the years 2016 and 2018 - 2020. First, the raw data is loaded from the file physiology_infection_stage_full_wideformat.csv and re-formatted (scaling variables, reordering factor levels etc.) before downstream analyses:

## Load data from csv file and code variable classes
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
df <- read.csv("./physiology_infection_stage_full_wideformat.csv", h = T, sep = ";",
    dec = ".") %>%
    mutate(Age_unz = as.numeric(Age_in_days)) %>%
    mutate(Age_unz.1 = as.numeric(Age_unz - days_resample)) %>%
    mutate(days_resample_unz = days_resample) %>%
    mutate(Age_in_days_unz = as.numeric(Age_in_days)) %>%
    mutate(Nest = as.factor(Nest)) %>%
    mutate(Date = chron(as.character(Date), format = "d/m/y")) %>%
    mutate(Infection_intensity.1 = as.factor(Infection_intensity.1)) %>%
    mutate(Infection_intensity.2 = as.factor(Infection_intensity.2)) %>%
    mutate(Prevalence2 = as.factor(ifelse(Infection_intensity.2 == 0, 0, 1))) %>%
    mutate(Prevalence1 = as.factor(ifelse(Infection_intensity.1 == 0, 0, 1))) %>%
    mutate(Breathing_rate = as.numeric(Breathing_rate)) %>%
    mutate(Sex = as.factor(Sex)) %>%
    mutate(Sampling_rank = as.factor(Sampling_rank)) %>%
    mutate(Weight_g = scale(as.numeric(Weight.2))) %>%
    mutate(Wing_cm = as.numeric(Wing.2)) %>%
    mutate(body_temperature = as.numeric(body_temperature)) %>%
    mutate(delta_body_condition = as.numeric(delta_body_condition)) %>%
    mutate(Ambient_Temperature_AvgC = scale(as.numeric(TemperatureAvgC))) %>%
    mutate(Treatment = as.factor(Treatment)) %>%
    mutate(Year = as.factor(Year)) %>%
    mutate(Growth_rate = as.numeric(Growth_rate)) %>%
    mutate(days_resample = scale(days_resample)) %>%
    mutate(Age_in_days = scale(as.numeric(Age_in_days))) %>%
    mutate(intensity_change = as.numeric(intensity_change)) %>%
    mutate(Diff_Inf_Class = factor(Diff_Inf_Class, levels = c("Uninfected", "Increase",
        "Peak", "Decrease")))

## Arrange data frame
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
df <- arrange(df, df$Diff_Inf_Class)

Effects on parasites

Investigating treatment (control vs Malarone) effects on the prevalence of Leucocytozoon parasites:

## Testing for differences in age at first and second sampling
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
## First
t.test(df$Age_unz.1[df$Treatment %in% "Malarone"], df$Age_unz.1[df$Treatment %in%
    "Control"])

# Second

t.test(df$Age_unz[df$Treatment %in% "Malarone"], df$Age_unz[df$Treatment %in% "Control"])

## Build contingency table: Infection prevalence and treatment: First sampling
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pre_treatment <- with(df, table(Prevalence1, Treatment))
prop.test(pre_treatment)
pairwise.prop.test(pre_treatment)

## Build contingency table: Infection prevalence and treatment: Second sampling
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
post_treatment <- with(df, table(Prevalence2, Treatment))
prop.test(post_treatment)
pairwise.prop.test(post_treatment)

## Proportion of infected individuals across time points
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
infected_treatment <- matrix(c(pre_treatment[2, ], post_treatment[2, ]), nrow = 2) %>%
    set_colnames(., c("First sampling", "Second sampling")) %>%
    set_rownames(., c("Control", "Malarone"))
prop.test(infected_treatment)
pairwise.prop.test(infected_treatment)

## Proportion of uninfected individuals across time points
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
uninfected_treatment <- matrix(c(pre_treatment[1, ], post_treatment[1, ]), nrow = 2) %>%
    set_colnames(., c("First sampling", "Second sampling")) %>%
    set_rownames(., c("Control", "Malarone"))
prop.test(uninfected_treatment)
pairwise.prop.test(uninfected_treatment)

Infection stages as explanatory variable

Exploring differences in physiological measures that are associated with the infection stage (increase, peak or decreasing) of tested individuals. All models account for a number of fixed effects and non-independence among nest mates.

Breathing rate

## Run model
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
lmer_br <- lmer(Breathing_rate ~ Diff_Inf_Class + Treatment + Age_in_days + days_resample +
    Weight_g + Sex + Ambient_Temperature_AvgC + Year + (1 | Nest), data = df)

## Obtain predicted values for each infection stage
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
mod_br <- get_model_data(lmer_br, type = "pred", terms = "Diff_Inf_Class") %>%
    mutate(x = factor(c("Uninfected", "Increase", "Peak", "Decrease"), levels = c("Uninfected",
        "Increase", "Peak", "Decrease")))

## Extract sample size for infection stage
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
n <- table(df$Diff_Inf_Class[!is.na(df$Breathing_rate)])

## ad sample size as label
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
mod_br <- mod_br %>%
    mutate(x = factor(c(paste0(x, "\nn= ", n)), levels = c(paste0(x, "\nn= ", n))))

mod_br <- mod_br[1:4, ]

## Plotting predicted values across infection stages
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fig_S1A <-  Fig_S1A <-
ggplot(mod_br) + aes(x, predicted) + geom_hline(yintercept = mean(mod_br$predicted,
    na.rm = T), linetype = "dashed") + labs(x = "", y = bquote("Breathing rate at T"[1])) +
    ylim(c(min(mod_br$conf.low) - 1.5, max(mod_br$conf.high) + 1.5)) + geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mod_br$conf.low,
    ymax = mod_br$conf.high), colour = "black", size = 2, width = 0.1) + geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mod_br$predicted -
    mod_br$std.error, ymax = mod_br$predicted + mod_br$std.error), size = 8, colour = wes_palette("Zissou1",
    4), width = 0, ) + geom_point(color = "black", size = 2) + theme_classic() +
    theme(legend.position = "none", axis.title = element_text(size = 18), axis.text = element_text(size = 16),
        axis.line.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank(), plot.margin = margin(0,
            0, 0, 0, "cm"), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold")) +
    geom_segment(size = 0.8, aes(x = 1, y = max(mod_br$conf.high) + 1, xend = 4,
        yend = max(mod_br$conf.high) + 1)) + geom_text(aes(x = 2.5, y = max(mod_br$conf.high) +
    1.5), label = "n.s.", size = 5)

  Breathing_rate ~ Infection_intensity.2 + Treatment + Age_in_days + days_resample +
    Weight_g + Sex + Ambient_Temperature_AvgC + Year + (1|Nest), data = df)

  Breathing_rate ~ 0 + Infection_intensity.2 + Treatment + Age_in_days + days_resample + 
    Weight_g + Sex + Ambient_Temperature_AvgC + Year + (1|Nest), data = df)

  mutate(higher_CI = conf.high) %>%

## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
tolres_deltamod = lm(delta_body_condition ~ Infection_intensity.2 * Diff_Inf_Class,
    data = tol_resdata)

## Robustness infection stages - summary graph of third sampled individuals
##------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Loading the dataset

third_sampled = readxl::read_excel("third_samples_indidividuals.xlsx")

# Computing the number of days between second and third sampling

third_sampled$Avg_third = third_sampled$Date.3 - third_sampled$Date.2

# Categorizing infection trends

third_sampled$Stage.1_2 = as.numeric(third_sampled$Infection_intensity.2) - as.numeric(third_sampled$Infection_intensity.1)

third_sampled$Stage.2_3 = as.numeric(third_sampled$Infection_intensity.3) - as.numeric(third_sampled$Infection_intensity.1)

third_sampled$comp_inf_stages = NA

for (i in 1:length(third_sampled$Date.1)) {
    # cat(third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i], 'versus', third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i],
    # '\n')
    if (third_sampled$Infection_intensity.1[i] == 0 & third_sampled$Infection_intensity.2[i] ==
        0 & third_sampled$Infection_intensity.3[i] == 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Unchanged_uninfected"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] > 0 & third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] == third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i]) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Unchanged_increase"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] < 0 & third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] == third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i]) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Unchanged_decrease"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] == 0 & third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] == third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i]) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Unchanged_stable"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] < 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] > 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Decrease_to_Increase"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] < 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] == 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Decrease_to_Stable"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] == 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] < 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Stable_to_Decrease"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] == 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] > 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Stable_to_Increase"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] > 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] < 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Increase_to_decrease"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] > 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] == 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Increase_to_stable"
        next
    }
    if (third_sampled$Stage.1_2[i] > 0 & third_sampled$Stage.2_3[i] > 0) {
        third_sampled$comp_inf_stages[i] = "Unchanged_increase"
        next
    }
}

third_sampled$comp_inf_stages_summary = ifelse(third_sampled$comp_inf_stages %in%
    c("Unchanged_increase", "Unchanged_decrease", "Unchanged_stable", "Unchanged_uninfected"),
    "Unchanged", "Differed")

# Plotting infection intensity across three sampling

strip = strip_themed(background_x = elem_list_rect(fill = ifelse(third_sampled$comp_inf_stages_summary %in%
    "Unchanged", "#30D40F", "#D41C0F")))

gg_trends = ggplot(third_sampled) + geom_point(aes(Date.1, Infection_intensity.1)) +
    geom_point(aes(Date.2, Infection_intensity.2)) + geom_point(aes(Date.3, Infection_intensity.3)) +
    facet_wrap2(~`Ring no`, scales = "free_x", strip = strip) + labs(title = "Individual infection course - three-time sampled",
    x = "Date", y = "Infection intensity")

Estimating measurement error of body temperature

## Loading repeated temperature measures
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
rTemp = read.csv2("./Repeatability_temperatures.csv", h = T, dec = ".") %>%
    mutate(ID = as.factor(ID)) %>%
    mutate(Date = as.Date(Date, format = "%d/%m/%y")) %>%
    mutate(Repeat = as.factor(Repeat))

## Estimating repeatability of paired measures
## -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
rpt(Temperature ~ (1 | ID), grname = "ID", data = rTemp, npermut = 1000, datatype = "Gaussian")
